vehicle_inventory.base_desc: One of the first mass market EVs, this quirky hatchback represented the vanguard of electrification.

vehicle_inventory.name: Fission
vehicle_inventory.base_desc: One of Wayne's last sedans for the U.S. market, this car seems to have been an office worker's commuter, given the briefcase of documents found under the passenger seat.

vehicle_inventory.name: Caldera
vehicle_inventory.base_desc: Based on the fading vinyl on the side, this one appears to have been a tradesperson's truck before things went south.

vehicle_inventory.name: W-350
vehicle_inventory.base_desc: The mudstains will never be out of the carpet, and it smells faintly of manure; this truck has had a long life of work already.

vehicle_inventory.name: Roadliner
vehicle_inventory.base_desc: (Orion) Continental is seldom known among the public, but had been a backbone of American infrastructure since before the interstates were even built. This one was part of a grocery fleet, and clearly saw many a suburban mile.

vehicle_inventory.name: Rumbug Pickup
vehicle_inventory.base_desc: This two door, long bed example of the classic rumbug is an icon of the former U.S. military. It fell out of favor around the turn of the millenium, as it lacked adequete armor to deal with IEDs when deployed across theatres in the Middle East.

vehicle_inventory.name: HEMTT
vehicle_inventory.base_desc: A 10-ton, 8x8 heavy tactical truck that first entered service with the U.S. Army in 1982.

cargo_inventory.name: MRE Boxes
cargo_inventory.base_desc: 12 pack of shitty, pre-collapse MREs. Absolutely disgusting, but they function as food. Barely.

cargo_inventory.name: Jerry Cans
cargo_inventory.base_desc: Just good ol', classic jerry cans. Not very space efficient, but small and convenient.

cargo_inventory.name: Water Jerry Cans
cargo_inventory.base_desc: Just good ol', classic jerry cans. Not very space efficient, but small and convenient. Painted blue, so that nobody accidentally puts fuel in this potable water container.

cargo_inventory.name: Water IBCs
cargo_inventory.base_desc: An aluminum intermediate bulk container of water. Painted blue, so that nobody accidentally puts fuel in this potable water container.

cargo_inventory.name: MRE Pallets
cargo_inventory.base_desc: A pallet of shitty, pre-collapse MREs. Absolutely disgusting, but they function as food. Barely.
